allDisconnectCallback



Pointer to user function callback. Returns the WLAN connection status as a parameter.



WLANNWCT_IPSTATUS_CT_AQRD - currently WLAN connected and IP acquired. 

WLANNWCT_IPSTATUS_CT_NAQRD - currently WLAN connected and IP not acquired. 

WLANNWCT_IPSTATUS_DISCT_AQRD - currently WLAN disconnected and IP acquired 

WLANNWCT_IPSTATUS_DISCT_NAQRD - currently WLAN disconnected and IP not acquired.
Example usage: Get current status of a network and set a callback for any disconnect events voidmyAllDisconnectCallbackFunc(WlanNetworkConnect_Status_TreturnStatus)
{
if(WLANNWCT_STATUS_DISCONNECTED==returnStatus)
{
//NetworkdisconnectionsuccessfullyfromWlanNetworkConnect_Disconnectfunction
printf("CallbackFunction:Adisconnecteventhashappened!\n\r");
}
}

//localvariables
Retcode_TretStatus;

if(WLANNWCT_IPSTATUS_DISCT_NAQRD
!=WlanNetworkConnect_GetIpStatus()
&&(WLANNWCT_IPSTATUS_DISCT_AQRD
!=WlanNetworkConnect_GetIpStatus()))
{
retStatus=WlanNetworkConnect_Disconnect();
printf("Finisheddisconnectionsuccessfully\n\r");
}

none







WLANNWCT_STATUS_CONNECTED - WLAN connected obtained after calling connect function. 

WLANNWCT_STATUS_DISCONNECTED - WLAN disconnected obtained after calling disconnect function.
